		<title>RSS block</title>
		<link>https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/rss-block/</link>
					<comments>https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/rss-block/#comments</comments>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Birgit Pauli-Haack]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sat, 23 Nov 2019 18:58:44 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Customization]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Widget blocks]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://wordpress.org/support/?post_type=helphub_article&#038;p=12167360</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Go back to the list of Blocks An RSS feed is a machine-readable version of the content of a blog or a website. With the RSS block, you can display content from any site’s RSS feed on your website. You can choose to display the Title, Author, Date, and Excerpt for each item in the [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p class="has-text-align-right has-small-font-size"><a href="https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/">Go back to the list of <strong>Blocks</strong></a></p>



<p>An RSS feed is a machine-readable version of the content of a blog or a website.</p>



<p>With the <em>RSS</em> block, you can display content from any site’s RSS feed on your website.  You can choose to display the Title, Author, Date, and Excerpt for each item in the feed. You can display the items in a list or as a grid in a set number of columns. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-video"><video controls src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/HelpHub-RSS-Block-August-2022.mp4"></video></figure>



<p class="has-extra-large-font-size">Steps to embed an RSS block</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>First, you need to know the URL of the RSS feed that you want to embed. Some websites display an orange icon <img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="512" height="512" class="wp-image-12167833" style="width: 18px" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/11/RSS-feed-icon.png" alt="" srcset="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/11/RSS-feed-icon.png 512w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/11/RSS-feed-icon-300x300.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2019/11/RSS-feed-icon-150x150.png 150w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px" /> with the link of the feed. You can usually find this icon together with social network icons.<br>Our example uses the feed of the <a href="https://wordpress.org/news/">News</a> section on WordPress.org. &nbsp;<a href="https://wordpress.org/news/feed">https://wordpress.org/news/feed</a></li>
</ol>



<ol class="wp-block-list" start="2">
<li>Click the <strong>Block Inserter</strong> (+) icon to add an <em>RSS</em> block to your WordPress page/post. Alternatively, you can type&nbsp;<kbd>/rss</kbd>&nbsp;and hit enter in a new&nbsp;<em>paragraph block</em>&nbsp;to add one quickly.</li>
</ol>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-1.png" alt="Adding RSS block via the WordPress slash command /rss" class="wp-image-16002203" width="268" height="133" srcset="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-1.png 536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-1-300x149.png 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 268px) 100vw, 268px" /></figure>



<p class="has-text-align-left has-background" style="background-color:#e5f5fa"><a href="https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/">Detailed instructions on adding blocks</a></p>



<ol class="wp-block-list" start="3">
<li>Paste the link of the RSS feed into the text box and click on the <strong>Use URL</strong> button</li>
</ol>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="430" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-2-1024x430.png" alt="Enter URL here user interface for the RSS block." class="wp-image-16002207" srcset="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-2-1024x430.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-2-300x126.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-2-768x323.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-2.png 1352w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>The <em>RSS</em> block now displays the titles of the feed items.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="361" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-3-1024x361.png" alt="Display of the RSS feed." class="wp-image-16002209" srcset="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-3-1024x361.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-3-300x106.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-3-768x271.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-3.png 1340w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>If you use an URL that can’t be embedded, the block shows the message <em>“RSS Error: WP HTTP Error: A valid URL was not provided.”</em>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="435" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-6-1024x435.png" alt="Example of a URL that cannot be used in the RSS block." class="wp-image-16002229" srcset="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-6-1024x435.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-6-300x127.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-6-768x326.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-6.png 1362w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>Use the options in the <strong>Block Toolbar</strong> and the controls in the <strong>Block Settings</strong> panel in your editor&#8217;s sidebar to fine-tune the display. </p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="block-toolbar">Block Toolbar</h2>



<p>Besides the <em>Mover</em> and <em>Drag &amp; Drop</em> handle, the Block Toolbar for the <em>RSS</em> block shows six other buttons:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Transform To</li>



<li>Change alignment</li>



<li>Edit RSS URL</li>



<li>List view</li>



<li>Grid view</li>



<li>More options</li>
</ul>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-4-1.png" alt="Block toolbar for the RSS block." class="wp-image-16002212" width="343" height="61" /></figure>



<p class="has-medium-font-size"><strong>Transform</strong> <strong>to</strong></p>



<p>You can transform the <em>RSS</em> block into Columns or a Group. Transforming to a group would give you the ability to change the background color around the embed.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-5-1-1024x358.png" alt="Transform options for the RSS block." class="wp-image-16002224" width="365" height="128" /></figure>



<p class="has-medium-font-size"><strong>Change alignment</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Align left</strong> &#8211; Make the block left-aligned.</li>



<li><strong>Align center</strong> &#8211; Make the block alignment centered.</li>



<li><strong>Align right </strong>&#8211; Make the block right-aligned.</li>



<li><strong>Wide width</strong> &#8211; Increase the width of the block beyond the content size.</li>



<li><strong>Full width</strong> &#8211; Extend the block to cover the full width of the screen.</li>
</ul>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-7.png" alt="Change alignment options for RSS block." class="wp-image-16002242" width="353" height="324" srcset="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-7.png 706w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-7-300x275.png 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 353px) 100vw, 353px" /></figure>



<p>The &#8220;Wide width&#8221; and &#8220;Full width&#8221; alignment settings must be enabled by your WordPress theme.&nbsp;</p>



<p class="has-medium-font-size"><strong>Edit RSS URL</strong></p>



<p>Via the edit URL, you can change the RSS feed URL in the block. Overwrite the existing URL and click on the <strong>Use URL</strong> button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-2-1024x430.png" alt="Edit RSS Feed URL in the block." class="wp-image-16002207" width="361" height="152" srcset="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-2-1024x430.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-2-300x126.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-2-768x323.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-2.png 1352w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 361px) 100vw, 361px" /></figure>



<p class="has-medium-font-size"><strong>List</strong> <strong>view</strong></p>



<p>The <strong>List view</strong> option displays the feed items in an unordered list. Use the Block settings controls to customize the <strong>List view</strong>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-8-1024x362.png" alt="List view for the RSS block." class="wp-image-16002253" width="359" height="127" srcset="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-8-1024x362.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-8-300x106.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-8-768x271.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-8.png 1330w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 359px) 100vw, 359px" /></figure>



<p class="has-medium-font-size"><strong>Grid&nbsp;view</strong></p>



<p>Display the feed items in a grid. Use the Block settings controls to adjust the number of columns and the other display options.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-9-1024x519.png" alt="Grid view for the RSS block." class="wp-image-16002254" width="371" height="188" srcset="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-9-1024x519.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-9-300x152.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-9-768x389.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/RSS-Feed-HelpHub-SS-9.png 1274w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 371px) 100vw, 371px" /></figure>



<p class="has-medium-font-size"><strong>More options</strong> </p>



<p>These controls give you the option to copy, duplicate, and edit your block as HTML.</p>



<p class="has-text-align-left has-background" style="background-color:#e5f5fa"><a href="https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/">Detailed instructions on adding blocks</a></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="settings">Block Settings</h2>



<p>Every block has specific options in the editor sidebar in addition to the options found in the block toolbar.&nbsp;<em>If you do not see the sidebar, simply click the &#8216;cog&#8217; icon.</em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-23-at-9.39.34-AM.png" alt="Cog icon to display the Block sidebar" class="wp-image-15765217" width="369" height="93" srcset="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-23-at-9.39.34-AM.png 492w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-23-at-9.39.34-AM-300x76.png 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 369px) 100vw, 369px" /></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image alignright size-full is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/11/197761657-5fa6467c-b73a-41ca-9c38-b79833af866e.png" alt="Block settings for the RSS block." class="wp-image-16209637" width="222" height="253" srcset="https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/11/197761657-5fa6467c-b73a-41ca-9c38-b79833af866e.png 302w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/11/197761657-5fa6467c-b73a-41ca-9c38-b79833af866e-263x300.png 263w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 222px) 100vw, 222px" /></figure>



<p class="has-medium-font-size"><strong>Settings</strong></p>



<p><strong>Number of items</strong>: Slider and number box to adjust the number of feed items you’d like to display. To change the number move the dot on the slider or update the number in the box next to it.</p>



<p><strong>Display author</strong>: Switch on/off the display of the author’s name&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Display date</strong>: Switch on/off the display of the published date of the feed items</p>



<p><strong>Display excerpt</strong>: Switch on/off the display of an excerpt from the feed items&#8217; content.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Max number of words in excerpt</strong>: Slider and number box to choose the maximum number of words that can be displayed in the excerpt. The minimum number is 10. This section is not visible if <strong>Display excerpt</strong> is in the OFF position.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Columns</strong>: Slider and number box to control the number of columns for the grid view. This option is only visible when you select the <strong>Grid view</strong> on the Block Toolbar.</p>



<p class="has-medium-font-size"><strong>Advanced</strong></p>



<p>The advanced tab lets you add a CSS class to your block, allowing you to write custom CSS and style the block as you see fit.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized"><img decoding="async" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/HCaeEAd-xkijY3husAGN8FkRfOokz6h-mLa1vQoT11JIf366WEE4Y3jtoy6CTOJGTpBZELgZPdIewg2ug8pURV5XtFciGwLHJiNwleOvlGte5WnWTug0SYe4p-qBR54_8oR1NwHM" alt="Advanced option in the selected Block" width="-274" height="-145" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Advanced option in the selected Block</figcaption></figure>



